---
name: markdown-html
version: 1.0.0
backends: [int]
---

# Markdown to HTML conformance

Pinned to `int` by `BUGS.md js-char-into-int-param`: on the v1 JS backend a `Char` passed
into an `Int` parameter stays boxed, so `markdown-core` itself misparses headings and lists
there and every block degrades to a paragraph. Widen this to `js` once that bug is fixed —
the renderer below is lane-agnostic and passes on the v2 JS bridge today.

[markdownToHtml, markdownInlineHtml, markdownSlug, markdownTitle, escapeHtml](std/markdown-html.ssc)

```scalascript
// Inline markup — the capability markdown-core deliberately lacks.
println(markdownInlineHtml("plain text"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("a **bold** word"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("an *italic* word"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("a `code` span"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("see [the guide](user-guide.md) now"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("an [external](https://example.com/a) link"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("**bold with `code` inside**"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("`**not bold** inside code`"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("**bold with [a link](one.md) inside**"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("[a **bold** label](two.md)"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("`code` then **bold** then *em*"))

// Degradation: an unclosed delimiter must stay literal, never emit an open tag.
println(markdownInlineHtml("unbalanced ** stays literal"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("unbalanced * stays literal"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("unbalanced ` stays literal"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("a [broken](link"))

// Escaping.
println(escapeHtml("<script>alert(\"x\" & 'y')</script>"))
println(markdownInlineHtml("5 < 6 && 7 > 2"))

// Anchors.
println(markdownSlug("Getting Started"))
println(markdownSlug("The `ssc` CLI — flags & options!"))

// Blocks.
println(markdownToHtml("# Title\n\nA paragraph with **bold**."))
println(markdownToHtml("- one\n- two **bold**"))
println(markdownToHtml("3. third\n4. fourth"))
println(markdownToHtml("```scala\nval x = 1 < 2\n```"))
println(markdownToHtml("| Name | Price |\n| :--- | ---: |\n| Free | 0 |"))
println(markdownToHtml("![Logo](./logo.png \"Brand\")"))
println(markdownToHtml("<!-- @meta component=PlanList -->"))

// A lone link line is an import to markdown-core but prose in a document.
println(markdownToHtml("[One](./one.md)"))

// Title extraction for nav labels.
println(markdownTitle("# The Title\n\nbody"))
println(markdownTitle("no heading here"))
```
